Great Nigeria Insurance Plc says it has implemented the company’s business continuity strategy as the world grapple with the rise in the number of COVID-19 infected individuals. A statement said the company’s business continuity strategy was hinged on safeguarding the health, wellbeing and safety of the lives of its customers and workforce, while ensuring the continuity of operations during the lockdown period. It noted that the Federal Government had directed the restriction of movements in Abuja Lagos,and Ogun states for 14 days to curb the spread of coronavirus disease. While commenting, the Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer, Great Nigeria Insurance Plc, Mrs Cecilia Osipitan, said in a bid to stay true to the company’s commitment of delivering quality service to our valued customers, alternative service channels have been made available for seamless access to all insurance products and services available under its stable. “On your mobile, please explore our USSD Platform by dialing *5076# for self-service, easy premium remittance, policy renewal and prompt claims settlement.” The company urged the public to stay safe, and ensure adherence to all precautionary measures given by the government and relevant health authorities. Copyright PUNCH.
